    },
    {
        "text": "in the northeastern u.s",
        "start": 3.36,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "you know it's autumn when deciduous",
        "start": 4.88,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "trees start sporting stunning yellows",
        "start": 6.48,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "oranges and reds but in europe",
        "start": 8.48,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "fiery orange and red leaves are less",
        "start": 10.32,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "common so autumn has a more yellow hue",
        "start": 12.16,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "now we don't know exactly why this is",
        "start": 14.24,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "it's a question that has perplexed",
        "start": 16.64,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "botanists for centuries",
        "start": 17.92,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "in fact they're not even sure why red",
        "start": 19.52,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "fall colors evolved in the first place",
        "start": 21.439,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "but they have two main hypotheses for",
        "start": 23.359,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "why only certain parts of the world get",
        "start": 25.279,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "to see autumn's finest displays",
        "start": 26.96,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "deciduous trees are those that drop",
        "start": 28.88,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "their leaves in the fall to help them",
        "start": 30.64,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "conserve energy and survive harsh winter",
        "start": 32.079,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "weather but before dropping their leaves",
        "start": 34.079,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "trees spend a few weeks reabsorbing",
        "start": 35.84,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "nutrients from them it'd be a shame to",
        "start": 37.68,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "let all the perfectly good stuff in",
        "start": 39.2,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "those leaves go to waste this includes",
        "start": 40.48,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "breaking down chlorophyll the pigment",
        "start": 42.16,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "that makes leaves green",
        "start": 43.92,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "as the green disappears you're left with",
        "start": 45.44,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "yellow to orange xanthophylls these",
        "start": 47.44,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "yellow pigments were there all along but",
        "start": 49.12,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "you couldn't see them for the green",
        "start": 50.96,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "at the same time however some trees",
        "start": 52.399,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "start making new pigments",
        "start": 54.559,
        "duration": 3.881
    },
    {
        "text": "specifically orange red and purple",
        "start": 56.079,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "anthocyanins and we're not sure why",
        "start": 58.44,
        "duration": 4.439
    },
    {
        "text": "if you're about to dump those leaves why",
        "start": 60.879,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "invest energy and turning them red",
        "start": 62.879,
        "duration": 2.961
    },
    {
        "text": "these pigments are more often seen in",
        "start": 64.4,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "trees native to eastern north america",
        "start": 65.84,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "and to parts of asia and south america",
        "start": 67.76,
        "duration": 3.359
    },
    {
        "text": "as well to be clear we're talking about",
        "start": 69.439,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "genetic differences",
        "start": 71.119,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "a given species will put out the same",
        "start": 72.32,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "fall colors wherever it grows we should",
        "start": 74.0,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "also note that the number of native",
        "start": 75.92,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "species with red leaves is actually",
        "start": 77.36,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "similar across north america and europe",
        "start": 79.28,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "but the really vivid species are more",
        "start": 81.6,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "abundant in north america the mystery is",
        "start": 83.68,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "why only some species turn red",
        "start": 86.0,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "hypothesis number one",
        "start": 88.0,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "says it's all about photo protection",
        "start": 89.52,
        "duration": 4.239
    },
    {
        "text": "that is the red pigment is acting like a",
        "start": 91.759,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "sort of sunscreen to protect the leaves",
        "start": 93.759,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "from light damage see chlorophyll's",
        "start": 95.52,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "normal job is to absorb photons of light",
        "start": 97.119,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "it absorbs their energy to make food for",
        "start": 99.6,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "the plant as chlorophyll degrades though",
        "start": 101.439,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "those energetic photons are left to",
        "start": 103.759,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "bounce around inside leaf cells",
        "start": 105.6,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "unchecked they can damage the enzymes",
        "start": 107.439,
        "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
        "text": "that are needed to recover precious",
        "start": 109.439,
        "duration": 2.081
    },
    {
        "text": "nutrients",
        "start": 110.88,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "red pigments are especially good at",
        "start": 111.52,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "absorbing stray photons",
        "start": 113.36,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "and mitigating that damage and they're",
        "start": 114.88,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "even more effective at lower",
        "start": 116.799,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "temperatures so",
        "start": 118.0,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "according to this hypothesis red",
        "start": 118.799,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "pigments help the trees absorb more",
        "start": 120.56,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "nutrients in the limited window before",
        "start": 122.159,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "the leaves drop one 2019 study found",
        "start": 124.0,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "that compared to europe",
        "start": 126.32,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "eastern north america has harsher light",
        "start": 127.6,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "conditions in autumn",
        "start": 129.52,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "and is more prone to cold snaps the",
        "start": 130.8,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "northeastern u.s also has a shorter",
        "start": 132.64,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "growing season so it could be that red",
        "start": 134.48,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "pigments gave trees there",
        "start": 136.319,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "an evolutionary advantage because it",
        "start": 137.76,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "helped them squeeze out a few more",
        "start": 139.44,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "nutrients from their",
        "start": 141.12,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "leaves as days got colder even as the",
        "start": 142.0,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "light stayed harsh",
        "start": 144.48,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "europe has had fewer of these selective",
        "start": 145.52,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "pressures so leaves stayed yellow the",
        "start": 147.2,
        "duration": 2.399
    },
    {
        "text": "trouble",
        "start": 149.2,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "is the evidence for this is kind of",
        "start": 149.599,
        "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
        "text": "mixed on one hand",
        "start": 151.68,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "trees do seem to intensify red pigment",
        "start": 153.04,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "production in response to cold sunny",
        "start": 155.2,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "days but sunlight and temperature",
        "start": 156.959,
        "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
        "text": "observations don't explain why you also",
        "start": 158.56,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "see colorful displays in japan where the",
