    },
    {
        "text": "question with this one",
        "start": 205.04,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "is why trees in new england would need",
        "start": 206.319,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "to signal to bugs more than others",
        "start": 208.159,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "some think it's historical basically",
        "start": 210.0,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "there used to be red trees in europe but",
        "start": 212.0,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "thanks to geographical barriers during",
        "start": 213.92,
        "duration": 3.039
    },
    {
        "text": "past glacial periods",
        "start": 215.68,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "they went extinct in north america the",
        "start": 216.959,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "mountain ranges run north to south",
        "start": 218.64,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "as ice sheets came down from the north",
        "start": 220.48,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "tree species were able to spread",
        "start": 222.64,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "southward into warmer climates the trees",
        "start": 224.0,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "in europe",
        "start": 226.08,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "couldn't do this their path to the south",
